y regentsedit in its early years uc had thirteen honorary regents with ten appointed in  honorary regents were full board members with the word honorary simply denoting their manner of selection that is they were elected to serve on the board by the other board members instead of being appointed by the governor some were then appointed to another term following their term as honorary regent by the governor one tompkins was reelected frederick low  th governor of california from  to  considered the father of the university of california andrew j moulder  state superintendent of public instruction – a founder of minns’ evening normal school in san francisco in  and of the first california state normal school in san jose approved by the legislature in  edward tompkins – samuel f butterworth – joseph m moss – william chapman ralston – founder of the bank of california john b felton – isaac friedlander – augustus j bowie – john s hager – california state senator and district judge united states senator from california – louis sachs – henry h haight  th governor of california signed the charter of the university of california on march   andrew smith hallidie  regarded as the inventor of the cable car and father of the present day san francisco cable car system president of the san francisco mechanics institute – and – notable legal casesedit regents of the university of california v bakke tarasoff v regents of the university of california moore v regents of the university of california usl v bsdi hamilton v regents of the university of california referencesedit  certificate of incorporation of the regents of the university of california  incorporation date as shown in the records of the california secretary of state  a b hollender allison  rundown on the regents city on a hill press retrieved    myers john  political road map so why can the uc regents thumb their noses at the legislature los angeles times issn  retrieved    california code of civil procedure section  requires that all civil actions must be prosecuted in the name of the real party in interest except as otherwise provided by statute  one of the few exceptions to this rule is in kentucky where actions against public universities can be brought in the institutions own name but can also be brought against the board see eg mitchell v university of kentucky et al sctg supreme court of kentucky april    california secretary of state entity number c  gutierrez melody asimov nanette  regents throw parties at uc’s expense san francisco chronicle retrieved    asimov nanette gutierrez melody  uc reverses policy won’t pick up tab for regents’ parties san francisco chronicle retrieved    brian pusser imanol ordorika  bringing political theory to university governance pdf universidad nacional autónoma de méxico retrieved    regents fact sheet  occupyucdavis webarchiveorg archived from the original on november   retrieved    welcome caldisorientationorg  justhostcom caldisorientationorg retrieved    members and advisors regents of the university of california retrieved    regent sherry l lansing  retrieved    a b c d koseff alexei  uc regents reconfirmed over criticisms of outofstate recruiting  the sacramento bee sacbeecom retrieved    regent bruce d varner  retrieved    sumers brian may   ben allen santa monica school board member seeks state senate seat daily breeze retrieved september     kalem stefanie parskys party easbbayexpresscom retrieved    u of california regent resigns abruptly  graduate students  the chronicle of higher education chroniclecom  retrieved    greg lucas  uc regent rejected by state senate  democrats say del junco too partisan sfgatecom retrieved    a b the regents of the university of california through the years days of cal the bancroft library  retrieved september     – a critical forum on research universities their finances their governance … their future » a former uc regent faults reporter’s profile of uc president yudof universityprobeorg  retrieve